## [2026-04-11] - Reliable Watched Status & Player Hotkeys

- **ACTION**: Implemented "Threshold Crossing" logic to resolve conflicts between auto-saving and manual watched status toggling.
- **STICKY STATUS**: Refactored both Rust backend (`library.rs`) and Svelte store (`media.ts`) to ensure the "Watched" status is persistent. Once marked, items remain watched regardless of rewinding or playhead resets to zero.
- **THRESHOLD CROSSING**: The auto-saver now only flags an item as "Watched" if the playhead specifically moves from below the threshold (e.g., 89%) to above it.
    - **UX**: This allows users to manually unmark a finished video as "Unwatched" using the 'W' key and have that choice respected even if the playhead remains at the end of the file.
- **GLOBAL PLAYER HOTKEY**: Added the **'W'** key to the `PlaybackFooter` keyboard handler. Users can now toggle the watched status of the active media item directly from the "Now Playing" interface without returning to the library.
- **BUG FIX**: Resolved a UI flickering issue where the frontend store would volatilely recalculate and overwrite the persistent "Watched" status on every progress update.
- **RATIONALE**: Solidifies the library management experience by prioritizing user intent over automatic calculations.

