## 2024-04-11: Implement hybrid window targeting for screenshot capture
- Updated `capture_screenshot` command in `src-tauri/src/commands/settings.rs` to use a multi-criteria approach instead of strictly requiring an exact PID match.
- This addresses issues where Tauri 2 uses separate processes for the backend and the webview UI, making the strict PID match fail.
- The new logic iterates through all windows and scores them based on PID match, Title match ("flux"), and window visibility (minimized or not). The highest scoring window is selected.
- Added comprehensive diagnostic logging (`println!`) to the terminal to detail all windows found and the final selected window.
- Updated the frontend `captureScreenshot` method in `FeedbackHUD.svelte` to better parse and log the backend error (`err`), helping clearly distinguish between "NotFound" and "Internal" errors.
